CBRE is pleased to present for sale the outstanding opportunity to purchase a property of scale (683* hectare), in a great location (Cowra/Canowindra corridor) with production flexibility as a true mixed farm or as a cropping platform.

Greenslopes has been operated as a true mixed farm with a focus on dual-purpose cropping, prime lambs and cattle.
Subdivided into 31* paddocks, Greenslopes is suited to rotations for grazing pressure to optimize pasture and crop utilization.

The 95* percent arability provides alternatives for enterprise selection. This is also supported by the quality soils best described as non-calcic brown earth.

The current enterprise selection has led to a pasture cropping blend of: 25* percent lucerne based, 49* percent pasture, 8* percent wheat, 10* percent grazing canola and 5* percent fallow.

Stock and domestic water is supplied via dams and the Billimari Bore Water Scheme reticulated to troughs around the property.
Annual average rainfall measured at the Cowra Agricultural Research Centre (Evans Street) is 630* millimetres.

Some planted timber laneways for stock shelter have been planted with the scattered timber on the residual of the property. Topography is rolling with a slope of less than 2* percent.

The homestead built in 1974 is four-bedroom (complete with built in robes), tile roof, brick veneer, internal single garage and detached shed, and an in-ground swimming pool. Set in an established garden with great views, a modernisation make-over may be required.

Improvements include 525* tonnes of grain storage, machinery shed, workshop/machinery shed, three-stand shearing shed, sheep and cattle yards and hayshed.

Greenslopes is being offered for sale by auction on 17th October 2019 at 11.00am AEDT at the Cowra Bowling Club.

Greenslopes represents a unique opportunity to purchase a property of scale and production flexibility in a blue-ribbon location.

Inspection is by appointment only with the Agent

CBRE Agribusiness is pleased to present for sale Stranraer, a quality dryland cropping and grazing lifestyle opportunity located at Cowra NSW.

Comprising 134.82* Hectares Stranraer is located 14*lineal kilometres north of Cowra and 65*lineal kilometres south-west of Orange.

Stranraer offers significant investment potential with the property sub-divided into three lots all with building entitlement, including the main lot 102 with existing dwelling.

Lot 102 - 45.123* Hectares
Lot 103 - 45.267* Hectares
Lot 1 - 44.435* Hectares

Plus, an enclosure road permit of 2.07* hectares on the southern boundary.

Stock and Domestic water is a feature with independent water meters for each lot. Water is supplied from the Billimari Bore Water Scheme that is administered by Cowra Shire Council.

Fresh water is supplied to the house from two 25,000* litre water storage tanks.

Stranraer is subdivided into twelve paddocks with existing fence-lines on new title boundaries.

Current farming practices have been cropping focused with grain production of canola, lupins, wheat and oats, whilst the self-watering area at the end of Clunes Creek has been used for lucerne hay production. Despite the dry conditions hay was cut off the self-watering paddocks on 25 November 2019.

Infrastructure includes: four silos (1x65T, 2x30T and 1x6T), steel sheep-yards, cattle-yards, complete with loading ramp, machinery shed, and a single-stand crutching shed.

Built in 1975 the corrugated iron roof, Hardi-plank dwelling of 206* square metres of living area, contains, three bedrooms, office, kitchen, dining room, family room, sitting room, laundry and two bathrooms.

Heating and cooling is supplied by three reverse cycle systems and additional gas heating. Hot water is electric, and three phase power is connected at sheds.

A fiberglass swimming pool of 9* by 3.6* metres is set in an easy- are back yard.

Internet service is wireless.

Stranraer has been listed for sale to allow the vendors to transition to full retirement.

Inspections of Stranraer are welcomed and can be arranged exclusively through the appointed selling agents.


*approximately
